<li id="cite_note-3"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFBorb.C3.A9lyS.C3.A1mson.2C_.C3.81rp.C3.A1d.3B_Schanda.2C_J.C3.A1nos2001">Borbély, Ákos; Sámson, Árpád; Schanda, János (December 2001). "<a href="http://www.knt.vein.hu/staff/schandaj/SJCV-Publ-2005/462.doc" class="external text" title="http://www.knt.vein.hu/staff/schandaj/SJCV-Publ-2005/462.doc" rel="nofollow">The concept of correlated colour temperature revisited</a>". <i>Color Research &amp; Application</i> <b>26</b> (6): 450–457. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1002%2Fcol.1065" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1002%2Fcol.1065" rel="nofollow">10.1002/col.1065</a></span><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.knt.vein.hu/staff/schandaj/SJCV-Publ-2005/462.doc" class="external free" title="http://www.knt.vein.hu/staff/schandaj/SJCV-Publ-2005/462.doc" rel="nofollow">http://www.knt.vein.hu/staff/schandaj/SJCV-Publ-2005/462.doc</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=The+concept+of+correlated+colour+temperature+revisited&amp;rft.jtitle=Color+Research+%26+Application&amp;rft.aulast=Borb%C3%A9ly&amp;rft.aufirst=%C3%81kos&amp;rft.au=Borb%C3%A9ly%2C+%C3%81kos&amp;rft.au=S%C3%A1mson%2C+%C3%81rp%C3%A1d%3B+Schanda%2C+J%C3%A1nos&amp;rft.date=December+2001&amp;rft.volume=26&amp;rft.issue=6&amp;rft.pages=450%E2%80%93457&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1002%2Fcol.1065&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.knt.vein.hu%2Fstaff%2Fschandaj%2FSJCV-Publ-2005%2F462.doc&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Color_temperature"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-4"><b><a href="#cite_ref-4" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFHyde1911">Hyde, Edward P. (June 1911). "A New Determination of the Selective Radiation from Tantalum (abstract)". <i>Physical Review (Series I)</i> (The American Physical Society) <b>32</b> (6): 632–633. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1103%2FPhysRevSeriesI.32.632" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1103%2FPhysRevSeriesI.32.632" rel="nofollow">10.1103/PhysRevSeriesI.32.632</a></span>.  "This existence of a color match is a consequence of there being approximately the same energy distribution in the visible spectra.".</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=A+New+Determination+of+the+Selective+Radiation+from+Tantalum+%28abstract%29&amp;rft.jtitle=Physical+Review+%28Series+I%29&amp;rft.aulast=Hyde&amp;rft.aufirst=Edward+P.&amp;rft.au=Hyde%2C+Edward+P.&amp;rft.date=June+1911&amp;rft.volume=32&amp;rft.issue=6&amp;rft.pages=632%E2%80%93633&amp;rft.pub=The+American+Physical+Society&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1103%2FPhysRevSeriesI.32.632&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Color_temperature"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-priest-5">^ <a href="#cite_ref-priest_5-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-priest_5-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFPriest1923">Priest, Irwin G. (1923). "<a href="http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?URI=josa-7-12-1175" class="external text" title="http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?URI=josa-7-12-1175" rel="nofollow">The colorimetry and photometry of daylight ·and incandescent illuminants by the method of rotatory dispersion</a>". <i><a href="/wiki/JOSA" title="JOSA">JOSA</a></i> <b>7</b> (12): 1175–1209<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?URI=josa-7-12-1175" class="external free" title="http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?URI=josa-7-12-1175" rel="nofollow">http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?URI=josa-7-12-1175</a></span>.  "<i>The color temperature of a source is the temperature at which a Planckian radiator would emit radiant energy competent to evoke a color of the same quality as that evoked by the radiant energy from the source in question</i>. The color temperature is not necessarily the same as the 'true temperature' of the source; but this circumstance has no significance whatever in the use of the color temperature as a means to the end of establishing a scale for the quality of the color of illuminants. For this purpose no knowledge of the temperature of the source nor indeed of its emissive properties is required. <i>All that is involved in giving the color temperature of any illuminant is the affirmation that the color of the luminant is of the same quality as the color of a Planckian radiator at the given temperature</i>.".</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=The+colorimetry+and+photometry+of+daylight+%C2%B7and+incandescent+illuminants+by+the+method+of+rotatory+dispersion&amp;rft.jtitle=%5B%5BJOSA%5D%5D&amp;rft.aulast=Priest&amp;rft.aufirst=Irwin+G.&amp;rft.au=Priest%2C+Irwin+G.&amp;rft.date=1923&amp;rft.volume=7&amp;rft.issue=12&amp;rft.pages=1175%E2%80%931209&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.opticsinfobase.org%2Fabstract.cfm%3FURI%3Djosa-7-12-1175&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Color_temperature"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-davis-6">^ <a href="#cite_ref-davis_6-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-davis_6-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFDavis1931"><a href="/wiki/Raymond_Davis,_Jr." title="Raymond Davis, Jr.">Davis, Raymond</a> (1931). "A Correlated Color Temperature for Illuminants". <i>National Bureau of Standards Journal of Research</i> <b>7</b>: 659–681.  "The ideal correlated colour temperature of a light source is the absolute temperature at which the Planckian radiator emits radiant energy component to evoke a colour which, of all Planckian colours, most closely approximates the colour evoked by the source in question.".</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=A+Correlated+Color+Temperature+for+Illuminants&amp;rft.jtitle=National+Bureau+of+Standards+Journal+of+Research&amp;rft.aulast=Davis&amp;rft.aufirst=Raymond&amp;rft.au=Davis%2C+Raymond&amp;rft.date=1931&amp;rft.volume=7&amp;rft.pages=659%E2%80%93681&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Color_temperature"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-judd-7">^ <a href="#cite_ref-judd_7-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-judd_7-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFJudd1931">Judd, Deane B. (1931). "<a href="http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?id=48631" class="external text" title="http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?id=48631" rel="nofollow">Chromaticity sensibility to stimulus differences</a>". <i><a href="/wiki/JOSA" title="JOSA">JOSA</a></i> <b>22</b> (2): 72–108<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?id=48631" class="external free" title="http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?id=48631" rel="nofollow">http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?id=48631</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Chromaticity+sensibility+to+stimulus+differences&amp;rft.jtitle=%5B%5BJOSA%5D%5D&amp;rft.aulast=Judd&amp;rft.aufirst=Deane+B.&amp;rft.au=Judd%2C+Deane+B.&amp;rft.date=1931&amp;rft.volume=22&amp;rft.issue=2&amp;rft.pages=72%E2%80%93108&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.opticsinfobase.org%2Fabstract.cfm%3Fid%3D48631&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Color_temperature"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-8"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFPriest1933">Priest, Irwin G. (February 1933). "<a href="http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?URI=josa-23-2-41" class="external text" title="http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?URI=josa-23-2-41" rel="nofollow">A proposed scale for use in specifying the chromaticity of incandescent illuminants and various phases of daylight</a>". <i><a href="/wiki/JOSA" title="JOSA">JOSA</a></i> <b>23</b> (2): 42<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?URI=josa-23-2-41" class="external free" title="http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?URI=josa-23-2-41" rel="nofollow">http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?URI=josa-23-2-41</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=A+proposed+scale+for+use+in+specifying+the+chromaticity+of+incandescent+illuminants+and+various+phases+of+daylight&amp;rft.jtitle=%5B%5BJOSA%5D%5D&amp;rft.aulast=Priest&amp;rft.aufirst=Irwin+G.&amp;rft.au=Priest%2C+Irwin+G.&amp;rft.date=February+1933&amp;rft.volume=23&amp;rft.issue=2&amp;rft.pages=42&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.opticsinfobase.org%2Fabstract.cfm%3FURI%3Djosa-23-2-41&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Color_temperature"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-9"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFJudd1933">Judd, Deane B. (January 1933). "<a href="http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?URI=josa-23-1-7" class="external text" title="http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?URI=josa-23-1-7" rel="nofollow">Sensibility to Color-Temperature Change as a Function of Temperature</a>". <i><a href="/wiki/JOSA" title="JOSA">JOSA</a></i> <b>23</b> (1)<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?URI=josa-23-1-7" class="external free" title="http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?URI=josa-23-1-7" rel="nofollow">http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?URI=josa-23-1-7</a></span>.  "Regarding (Davis, 1931): This simpler statement of the spectral-centroid relation might have been deduced by combining two previous findings, one by Gibson (see footnote 10, p. 12) concerning a spectral-centroid relation between incident and transmitted light for daylight filters, the other by Langmuir and Orange (Trans. A.I.E.E., 32, 1944–1946 (1913)) concerning a similar relation involving reciprocal temperature. The mathematical analysis on which this latter finding is based was given later by Foote, Mohler and Fairchild, J. Wash. Acad. Sci. 7, 545–549 (1917), and Gage, Trans. I.E.S. 16, 428–429 (1921) also called attention to this relation.".</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Sensibility+to+Color-Temperature+Change+as+a+Function+of+Temperature&amp;rft.jtitle=%5B%5BJOSA%5D%5D&amp;rft.aulast=Judd&amp;rft.aufirst=Deane+B.&amp;rft.au=Judd%2C+Deane+B.&amp;rft.date=January+1933&amp;rft.volume=23&amp;rft.issue=1&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.opticsinfobase.org%2Fabstract.cfm%3FURI%3Djosa-23-1-7&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Color_temperature"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-10"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFJudd1935">Judd, Deane B. (January 1935). "<a href="http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?URI=josa-25-1-24" class="external text" title="http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?URI=josa-25-1-24" rel="nofollow">A Maxwell Triangle Yielding Uniform Chromaticity Scales</a>". <i><a href="/wiki/JOSA" title="JOSA">JOSA</a></i> <b>25</b> (1): 24–35<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?URI=josa-25-1-24" class="external free" title="http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?URI=josa-25-1-24" rel="nofollow">http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?URI=josa-25-1-24</a></span>.  "An important application of this coordinate system is its use in finding from any series of colors the one most resembling a neighboring color of the same brilliance, for example, the finding of the nearest color temperature for a neighboring non-Planckian stimulus. The method is to draw the shortest line from the point representing the non-Planckian stimulus to the Planckian locus.".</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=A+Maxwell+Triangle+Yielding+Uniform+Chromaticity+Scales&amp;rft.jtitle=%5B%5BJOSA%5D%5D&amp;rft.aulast=Judd&amp;rft.aufirst=Deane+B.&amp;rft.au=Judd%2C+Deane+B.&amp;rft.date=January+1935&amp;rft.volume=25&amp;rft.issue=1&amp;rft.pages=24%E2%80%9335&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.opticsinfobase.org%2Fabstract.cfm%3FURI%3Djosa-25-1-24&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Color_temperature"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-11"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFOSA_Committee_on_Colorimetry1944">OSA Committee on Colorimetry (November 1944). "<a href="http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?URI=josa-34-11-633" class="external text" title="http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?URI=josa-34-11-633" rel="nofollow">Quantitative data and methods for colorimetry</a>". <i><a href="/wiki/JOSA" title="JOSA">JOSA</a></i> <b>34</b> (11): 633–688<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?URI=josa-34-11-633" class="external free" title="http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?URI=josa-34-11-633" rel="nofollow">http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?URI=josa-34-11-633</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Quantitative+data+and+methods+for+colorimetry&amp;rft.jtitle=%5B%5BJOSA%5D%5D&amp;rft.aulast=OSA+Committee+on+Colorimetry&amp;rft.au=OSA+Committee+on+Colorimetry&amp;rft.date=November+1944&amp;rft.volume=34&amp;rft.issue=11&amp;rft.pages=633%E2%80%93688&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.opticsinfobase.org%2Fabstract.cfm%3FURI%3Djosa-34-11-633&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Color_temperature"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> (recommended reading)</li>
